<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="poly2mask" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>poly2mask</refname><refpurpose>Rasterize a polygon into a binary mask.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>mask = poly2mask(x, y, rows, cols)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>x, y</term><listitem><para>Matching polygon vertex coordinates in one-based column/row image coordinates.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>rows, cols</term><listitem><para>Positive output image dimensions.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>mask</term><listitem><para>Boolean polygon mask.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>poly2mask</function> uses an even-odd polygon fill rule and treats image row 1 as the top row.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[x = [2 6 6 2]; y = [2 2 6 6]; mask = poly2mask(x, y, 8, 8); imshow(mask);]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="bwselect">bwselect</link></member><member><link linkend="imroi">imroi</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Function introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
